<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0496 </DOCNO><TEXT>There is only a small reported experience with digital subtraction angiography(DSA) in pediatric patients. Yet, the technique has generated a significantinterest among pediatric radiologists and promises widespread applicationto pediatric diagnosis in coming years. This short communication: (1)reviews the literature on pediatric DSA; (2) discusses methods and theunique problems in performing such studies in children; and (3) speculateson future developments and pediatric applications of this technique.</TEXT></DOC>